'''Crealogix Group''' (own spelling: CREALOGIX) is a [[Swiss]] [[software]] company headquartered in [[Zurich, Switzerland]], which develops and implements [[Financial Technology]] ([[FinTech]]) solutions for banks. The focus is placed on customer needs for mobility, security, personalised advice and education within a comprehensive [[user experience]].<ref>[https://www.finews.asia/finance/27663-crealogix-robo-adviser-hauck-aufhaeuser-fintech''Crealogix sells Robo Adviser to Private Bank'']. In: FinewsAsia, 29 October 2018. Retrieved 24 November 2018.</ref><ref>[https://www.marketscreener.com/CREALOGIX-HOLDING-AG-68705/news/Brandon-Hall-Group-Excellence-Awards-CREALOGIX-wins-the-Digital-Learning-Gold-Award-in-the-field-of-25371001/''Brandon Hall Group Excellence Awards: CREALOGIX wins the Digital Learning Gold Award in the field of compliance'']. In: MarketScreener by 4-traders, 26 October 2017. Retrieved 24 November 2018.</ref><ref>[https://www.finanzen.ch/nachrichten/aktien/crealogix-wins-2018-systems-in-the-city-award-for-digital-solutions-in-uk-wealth-management-1027377746''Crealogix wins 2018 Systems in the City Award for Digital Solutions in Wealth Management]. In: Finanzen.ch, 18 July 2018. Retrieved 24 November 2018.</ref>Established in 1996, the Group has over 500 employees worldwide and offices in [[Switzerland]] (Zurich, Berne, Bubikon), [[Germany]] (Stuttgart, Puchheim, Jever, Coburg), [[United Kingdom]] (London, Winchester), [[Singapore]] and Barcelona.<ref name="Mitarbeiterzahl"/> The [[shares]] of Crealogix Holding AG (CLXN) are traded on the [[SIX Swiss Exchange]].<ref name="SIX Swiss Exchange">[http://www.six-swiss-exchange.com/shares/security_info_en.html?id=CH0011115703CHF4''Crealogix Holding AG'']. Six Swiss Exchange. Retrieved 22 July 2015.</ref>
==History== The company was founded in 1996 in [[Switzerland]] by Bruno Richle (Executive Chairman), Dr. Richard Dratva (Chief Strategy Officer, Vice Chairman), Peter Süsstrunk (Senior Management) and Daniel Hiltebrand.<ref>[https://crealogix.com/ch/en/company/management/''Organisation - Management'']. CREALOGIX Holding AG. Retrieved 23 May 2018.</ref> The IPO followed in 2000.<ref name="SIX Swiss Exchange"/> Crealogix changed from an initial service provider to a software product manufacterer, providing [[solution]]s in the fields of online and mobile [[banking]] & [[payment]]s, as well as [[digital learning]] & education. <ref name=''Restults16''/><ref>[http://www.banking-gateway.com/projects/future-banking-crealogix-thomas-avedik/index.html''Crealogix: put the pedal to the metal – Thomas Avedik'']. In: Banking Gateway, N/A. Retrieved 24 November 2018.</ref> Additionally the company has developed a focus on the [[financial industry]].<ref name=''Restults16''>[https://www.six-group.com/exchanges/issuers/services/tensid_news_en.html?id=a331bcb3''CREALOGIX reports strong growth'']. In: Six Swiss Exchange, 20 September 2016. Retrieved 24 November 2018.</ref><ref>[https://www.edisoninvestmentresearch.com/?ACT=18&ID=16474&LANG= ''CREALOGIX Group Leader in digital banking technology'']. In: Edison Investment Research, 13 June 2016. Retrieved 24 November 2018.</ref> In 2011 Crealogix acquired the [[e-banking]] business unit of 'abaXX' from Cordys Deutschland AG.<ref>[https://www.marketscreener.com/CREALOGIX-68705/news/CREALOGIX-acquires-abaXX-expands-lead-in-e-banking-and-strengthens-European-business-13732992/'' CREALOGIX acquires abaXX; expands lead in e-banking and strengthens European business'']. In: MarketScreener by 4-traders, 30 July 2011. Retrieved 24 November 2018.</ref> In 2012, the entire AdviceManager product business was acquired from the German company C1 FinCon.<ref>[https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=222686802''Company Overview of C1 Fincon GmbH, AdviceManager Product Business'']. In: Bloomberg, 05 October 2012. Retrieved 24 November 2018.</ref> In 2014, the company established new locations in [[London]], [[Vienna]] and [[Singapore]].<ref>[https://www.prnewswire.co.uk/news-releases/crealogix-group-has-established-subsidiaries-in-london-and-singapore-256294261.html''Crealogix has established subsidiaries in London and Singapore'']. In: PRNewswire, 23 April 2014. Retrieved 3 July 2015.</ref> In January 2015, it acquired the company MBA Systems in UK.<ref name="IBS MBA Systems">[https://ibsintelligence.com/ibs-journal/ibs-news/crealogix-acquires-mba-systems-to-gain-uk-foothold/''Crealogix acquires MBA Systems to gain UK foothold'']. In: IBS Intelligence, 28 January 2015. Retrieved 24 November 2018.</ref> Thomas Avedik, the former head of the 'Swiss Digital Banking' business unit, was appointed CEO of the Crealogix Group as of 1 January 2016.<ref>[https://files.crealogix.com/group/financial-reports/2016/CREALOGIX-Annual-Report-2015-16.pdf''Letter to Shareholders'']. In: CREALOGIX Annual Report 2015/2016, 20 September 2016. Retrieved 24 November 2018.</ref> In January 2018, the Group acquired 100 percent of the shares of Innofis, a Barcelona-based digital banking provider.<ref>[https://www.bloomberg.com/press-releases/2018-01-09/the-gateway-into-the-middle-east-crealogix-acquires-innofis-jc7qbjna ''The Gateway into the Middle East - CREALOGIX Acquires Innofis'']. On: Bloomberg, 9 January 2018. Retrieved 23 May 2018. </ref> A short time later, it takes over ELAXY Business Solution & Services completely from the German IT service provider Fiducia & GAD IT AG.<ref name="Finextra">[https://www.finextra.com/pressarticle/74573/crealogix-takes-on-further-shares-in-elaxy-from-fiducia—gad''Crealogix takes on further shares in Elaxy from Fiducia & GAD'']. In: Finextra, 5 July 2018. Retrieved 09 July 2018.</ref> With the overall takeover, Crealogix exercised an option that was already agreed within the framework of the initial investment in 2015.<ref>[https://ibsintelligence.com/ibs-journal/ibs-news/crealogix-acquires-majority-stake-in-fiducia-gads-elaxy-advisory-subsidiary/''Crealogix acquires majority stake in Fiducia & GAD’s Elaxy advisory subsidiary'']. In: IBS Intelligence, 22 October 2015. Retrieved 24 November 2018. </ref> The investments in ELAXY Financial Software & Solutions remain unchanged; Crealogix holds 80% and Fiducia & GAD continues to hold 20%.<ref name="Finextra"/>
