'''Inovallée''' (contraction in French for the words innovation and valley) is a [[science park]] located at [[Meylan]] and [[Montbonnot-Saint-Martin]] near [[Grenoble]] in France.

Created in 1972 with the acronym ZIRST,<ref>[http://acronyms.thefreedictionary.com/ZIRST acronym ZIRST.]</ref><ref>[http://www.lesechos.fr/15/04/2005/LesEchos/19393-025-ECH_a-grenoble--la-zirst-va-etendre-sa-zone-d-influence.htm lesechos.fr, A Grenoble, la ZIRST va étendre sa zone d'influence.] {{fr}}</ref> it becomes Inovallée in 2005 and houses primarily companies in the fields of [[information and communications technology]]. In 2014, there are more than 362 companies and 11,174 people working in the park.<ref>[http://lessor.fr/inovallee-confirme-sa-forte-attractivite-10150.html lessor.fr, Inovallée confirme sa forte attractivité] {{fr}}</ref>

Inovallée also benefits from the close proximity of the [[Université Grenoble Alpes]], [[Grenoble Institute of Technology]] and the [[Polygone Scientifique]].<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=K39x4O2dHjM Inovallée]</ref>

==Companies and institutions==
The major companies located at Inovallée are [[X|Xerox Research Centre Europe]],<ref>[http://www.greenit.fr/2015/05/14/air-liquide-teste-le-coach-personnalise-print-awareness-tool-de-xerox/ greenit.fr, Air Liquide teste le coach personnalisé Print Awareness Tool de Xerox.] {{fr}}</ref> [[Orange S.A.|Orange labs]], [[Dolphin Integration]], [[Mirantis]], [[Schneider Electric]], [[Salesforce.com]]<ref>[http://www.lemagit.fr/actualites/2240200572/Salesforce-ouvre-un-centre-de-RD-a-Grenoble lemagit.fr, Salesforce ouvre un centre de R&D à Grenoble.] {{fr}}</ref> and also the [[French Institute for Research in Computer Science and Automation]].

